  "prompt": "Why was MM kalburgi killed?",
  "response": "M. M. Kalburgi, an Indian scholar and former vice-chancellor of Kannada University, was killed on August 30, 2015. His murder is widely believed to be linked to his outspoken views on religious and cultural issues. Kalburgi was a vocal critic of superstition and orthodox religious practices, which drew ire from certain fundamentalist groups.\n\nHis assassination was part of a series of attacks on intellectuals and rationalists in India, including the killings of Govind Pansare and Narendra Dabholkar, who were also involved in promoting rationalism and criticizing religious orthodoxy. These attacks triggered significant public outcry and concerns over freedom of expression and the safety of intellectuals in the country.\n\nThe motive behind Kalburgi's murder is generally thought to be connected to his critical viewpoints, though the specific individuals and groups responsible for orchestrating the attack have been a matter of investigation and public debate.",
